com.ibm.team.workitem.common.expression.variables

Interface IAttributeVariable<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.ibm.team.workitem.common.internal.expression.IAttributeValue
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractAttributeVariable, AnyoneVariable, AttributeParameterVariable, CurrentMilestoneVariable, CurrentUserVariable, MyCategoriesVariable, ProjectAreasVariable, RelativeDateVariable, StatusVariable, UnassignedVariable, WorkItemTypeVariable

    public interface IAttributeVariable<T>
extends com.ibm.team.workitem.common.internal.expression.IAttributeValue
    Can be used inside attribute expressions instead of a constant value (e.g. current user, current date,...).
    Since:
    0.5

      • evaluate

        java.util.Collection<T> evaluate(IEvaluationContext context,
                               org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor monitor)
                                 throws TeamRepositoryException
        Evaluates the variable in a specific evaluation context. This is a potentially long-running operation. Is allowed to return a Collection containing ItemHandles, Strings or Integers.
        Parameters:
        context - The evaluation context
        monitor - Indicates progress, can be null.
        Returns:
        The evaluated value of the variable at the time.
        Throws:
        TeamRepositoryException

      • isProjectScoped

        boolean isProjectScoped()
        Returns true if the resolution of this variable uses context.getProjectArea() in evaluate() call or false otherwise. AnyoneVariable will return false while CurrentMilesoneVariable will return true for example.
